Q22. Write AJAX program to print movie details by selecting an Actor’s name. Create tables Movie and
Actor with 1:M cardinality as
follows: Movie (mno,mname, release_year) Actor (ano,aname) [Use PostgreSQL] Solution

Answer::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

<?php
$aname=$_GET['aname'];
$con=pg_connect("host=localhost port=5432 dbname=sakshi user=postgres password=tybcs");
$q="select * from movie m,actor a where m.ano=a.ano and a.name='$aname';";
$res=pg_query($con,$q);
while($row=pg_fetch_row($res))
{
echo"row[0] $row[1] $row[2]";
}
pg_close($con);
?>
<html>
<head>
<script>
function load(aname)
{
var x=new XMLHttpRequest();
x.open("GET","prog1.php?aname="+aname,true);
x.send();
x.onreadystatechange=function(){
if(x.readyState==4 && x.status==200)
{
document.getElementById("res").innerHTML=x.responseText;
}
}
}
</script>
</head>
<body>
<select name="aname" onchange=load(this.value)>
<option value="a">a</option>
<option value="b">b</option>
</select>
<div id="res"></div>
</body>
</html>
